—Endemic to the Cordillera de Talamanca in 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFDF7F369D1DE226D3A2FED9" box="[1068,1200,345,371]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
; to be looked for in adjacent 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFDF7F369830E2FFD670FE30" box="[257,354,384,410]" name="Panama" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Panama</collectingCountry>
. Known from only two collections in disturbed humid montane forests (with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369DC6E2FFD281FE30" box="[1271,1427,384,410]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369DC6E2FFD24BFE33" box="[1271,1369,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Quercus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
) at 
<quantity id="4CD1EF8FFFDF7F369982E2D9D64AFE6A" box="[179,344,422,448]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="m" value="2450.0" valueMax="2500.0" valueMin="2400.0">2400–2500 m</quantity>
