).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFDF7F3699F7E165D7CCFD5C" blockId="26.[151,1437,152,1338]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F3699F7E165D607FD9E" bold="true" box="[198,277,538,564]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369802E165D6E2FD99" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" box="[307,496,538,563]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369802E165D6E2FD99" box="[307,496,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Sticherus fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a medium-sized species with pinnae 
<quantity id="4CD1EF8FFFDF7F369AF5E165D328FD9E" box="[964,1082,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="cm" value="22.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="15.0">15–30 cm</quantity>
long, short, simple aphlebiae, persistent dark scales on the rachises, rather short, lanceolate distal branches with flat segments, and abundant, dark lateral scales on the abaxial branches. These dark axial scales contrast with the dull brown arachnoid scales of the segment surfaces. The bud scales are narrowly lanceolate and mostly rigid with translucent bases, whereas the midvein scales are rectangular and only apically rigid (especially the proximal ones).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFDF7F3699F7E07DD28EFBD2" blockId="26.[151,1437,152,1338]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F3699F7E07DD690FCB1" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" box="[198,386,770,795]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F3699F7E07DD690FCB1" box="[198,386,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Sticherus fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369BA0E07DD43AFCB1" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1980" baseAuthorityName="Christ" box="[657,808,770,795]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevipubis">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369BA0E07DD43AFCB1" box="[657,808,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. brevipubis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369A07E07DD4DAFCB1" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1990" box="[822,968,770,795]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tepuiensis">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369A07E07DD4DAFCB1" box="[822,968,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. tepuiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369AE7E07DD36DFCB1" authorityName="Ostergaard &amp; Ollgaard" authorityYear="2001" box="[982,1151,770,795]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aurantiacus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369AE7E07DD36DFCB1" box="[982,1151,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. aurantiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369D8EE07DD230FCB1" baseAuthorityName="Stolze" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[1215,1314,770,795]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulvus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369D8EE07DD230FCB1" box="[1215,1314,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. fulvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369C01E07DD604FCE8" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1980" baseAuthorityName="Christ" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevipubis">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369C01E07DD604FCE8" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Sticherus brevipubis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369889E056D530FCE8" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" box="[440,546,809,834]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369889E056D530FCE8" box="[440,546,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in being generally larger, having much more reduced aphlebiae (or even lacking aphlebiae), reduced internal proximal segments on all branches (i.e., the segments do not overlap as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F3699A6E008D7EFFC3A" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" box="[151,253,887,912]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F3699A6E008D7EFFC3A" box="[151,253,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), more revolute segment margins, and paler segment scales. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369AF5E008D3BEFC3A" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1990" box="[964,1196,887,912]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tepuiensis">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369AF5E008D3BEFC3A" box="[964,1196,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Sticherus tepuiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks aphlebiae, has narrower and longer branches, glabrous rachises, and has shorter and scattered lateral scales abaxially on the branches. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369824E0BBD531FC77" authorityName="Ostergaard &amp; Ollgaard" authorityYear="2001" box="[277,547,964,989]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aurantiacus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369824E0BBD531FC77" box="[277,547,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Sticherus aurantiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having longer, more linear distal branches, reduced proximal internal segments, and has scales of generally paler, duller colors and thinner texture. The pattern of scale darkening of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369803E76ED685FB80" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" box="[306,407,1041,1066]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369803E76ED685FB80" box="[306,407,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369B5DE76ED5DCFB80" baseAuthorityName="Stolze" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[620,718,1041,1066]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulvus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369B5DE76ED5DCFB80" box="[620,718,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. fulvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and specimens with strongly rigid scales of the latter species may be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F36989AE747D507FBFB" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" box="[427,533,1080,1105]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F36989AE747D507FBFB" box="[427,533,1080,1105]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369B93E747D41AFBFB" baseAuthorityName="Stolze" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[674,776,1080,1105]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulvus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369B93E747D41AFBFB" box="[674,776,1080,1105]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. fulvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is generally larger, has shorter and more ovate scales, more strongly reduced, auricle-like, non-overlapping proximal internal segments, and usually lacks aphlebiae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFDF7F3699F7E7FAD367FA90" blockId="26.[151,1437,152,1338]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F3699F7E7FAD694FB34" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" box="[198,390,1157,1182]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F3699F7E7FAD694FB34" box="[198,390,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Sticherus fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from two collections from 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFDF7F369ABCE7FAD307FB35" box="[909,1045,1157,1183]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. It is very unlikely that the 
<typeStatus id="5492FCC8FFDF7F369C58E7FAD289FB35" box="[1385,1435,1157,1183]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">type</typeStatus>
specimen represents a hybrid, because the only potential parental taxa in 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFDF7F369D30E7D3D391FB6C" box="[1025,1155,1196,1222]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
would be 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369C33E7D3D28EFB6F" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1980" baseAuthorityName="Christ" box="[1282,1436,1196,1221]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevipubis">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369C33E7D3D28EFB6F" box="[1282,1436,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. brevipubis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F3699F8E7ACD67CFB46" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Desv." box="[201,366,1235,1260]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F3699F8E7ACD67CFB46" box="[201,366,1235,1260]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the known hybrids between these two species are much larger than 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFDF7F369DF5E7ACD238FB46" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" box="[1220,1322,1235,1260]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFDF7F369DF5E7ACD238FB46" box="[1220,1322,1235,1260]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and have larger aphlebiae. The confusion surrounding this species complex (see also Stolze 1981) can be resolved only through a detailed biosystematic study involving cytotaxonomic and molecular data.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
